    <!-- message -->
    <div align="left" id="post_message_514932">So due to various ******** drama with the group I normally play with on Saturday nights, I'm thinking of stepping entirely away from those guys and running something for my best friend and some others. <br />
<br />
I've got quite a few Pathfinder supplements including the core book, advanced player guide, ultimate magic, and some setting books (I really like their setting).<br />
<br />
Does anyone have any experience with the Adventure Paths? <br />
<br />
There were a few (Carrion Crown, Legacy of Fire) which sounded interesting, but I'm specifically looking for something that would work (or easily adapt) to a group of probably 2-3 adventurers, and a GM (me) who's completely new to that side of the table. Aside from a few Champions: New Millenium games about 13 years ago, I've got no experience GM'ing.</div>
    <!-- / message -->
    
    
