    <div align="left">
	<hr align="left" width="100%" />

    <!-- message -->
    <div align="left" id="post_message_515991">If you go for an adventure path, the Council of Thieves series seems pretty awesome. It's very urban (all centered around one city and its outskirts), and has a lot of variety to it. The second adventure is basically a huge play for the characters to act in while they're infiltrating someplace. Reminded me of FF3/6..<br />
<br />
That said, if your group's more into straight dungeon crawls, it's probably not the AP for you :D I guess some of the earlier ones (Rise of the Runelords) had a more &quot;classic&quot; feel.</div>
