    <div align="left">
	<hr align="left" width="100%" />

    <!-- message -->
    <div align="left" id="post_message_524236">That's a pretty good idea.<br />
<br />
I guess I just don't like the idea that in Pathfinder you can just go &quot;well, I've got the feat, and a pile of gold, guess I can make any magic item I want&quot;.  I feel like there's should be another resource at play there besides purely cash.<br />
<br />
It also always bothers me how the crafting of the items themselves was never relevant to making magic items.  The most powerful magic sword in the game can still be made by someone who can hit a 15 on a smithing roll.<br />
<br />
Kinda makes the whole concept of the famous master smith kind of pointless.</div>
    <!-- / message -->
    
    
    <br>
