</div>My group's Pathfinder house rules let the creater of magic items spend 'time', or life-force in the form of aging. So they don't lose experience, but they do get older quicker. This is one of the reasons why Elven crafted items are so prolific compared to other races. Also why Liches have an edge with nasty magical items.</div>
